</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmmm</span><hr size=1> I think a point is being missed my some.<br>
<br>
Most other classes mainly use their defensive to escape, because most of the time they aren't tanking. Knights do tank, but if you consider DA their defensive, they can't tank with it (only escape).<br>
<br>
Here's what I think people are trying to get at:<br>
When Lordgoofydragon (don't know if this is a good example, but I like saying it) decides he's going to finish off a rogue after finishing of a warrior. With his defensive, the rogue can buy the raid 10 seconds + however longer he can survive, to get things back under control. That's about 10-15 seconds where no one is dieing.<br>
<br>
If a paladin finds herself the victim of Goofydragon, and she used DA or the /disc, she isn't buying the raid any time since now LordGoofy is going to turn his attention to someone else. In otherwords, people are still dying in those 18 seconds.<br>
<br>
While this may be acceptable for some classes (clerics for example), it really shouldn't be considered the 'defensive' for the games second best tanks.<br>
<br>
I'm curious, Gilfalas, how many clerics+warriors does it take to tank Derakor the Vindicator  for 4.5 minutes? If that number is &lt; 15 then this would seem like a far trade off. X number of well coordinated knight classes taking no damage, could be a viable second option to X-Y total number of clerics and warriors taking damage but healing it up. If not, then the length of the disc could be reduced (10-15 seconds?), so that would be a possible strategy, but definately not the best one.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirlageholyblaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Lage Holyblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/3/02 11:25:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15416.topic&index=94>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmmm</span><hr size=1> Thanks Cylria.  Better stated then I could have.<br>
