</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uqualtarshylok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qualtar Shylok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/4/02 11:10:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15416.topic&index=98>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: but Gilfalas</span><hr size=1> Ill come  back to read all the posts later, but from what I read it seems folks are debating the difference between our offense and defense skills as compared to other classes.<br>
<br>
I think for the most part we are balanced offensively.  We dont do near as good as good as damage, but Verant has ensured that we get the best weapons in game to assist with our damage output.  Any melee class would love to be able to duel weild a few 24/22 1hs weapons.<br>
<br>
Defensively, we could use a little twinking in the uber encounters only.  For the most part I can tank any mob in game given the same support a warrior gets (cleric/chanters), except for uber mobs like gods or dragons, and actually require less support than a similar equipped warrior would need (we require less healing, faster regen).  A small twink to our defensive disc would prolly be the simplest answer.  However, the tradeoff for being able to tank better than a warrior on normal exp mobs vs being able to not tank on uber mobs may actually make us balanced defensively.   <p><BR><p align="left"><font face="Arial" color="#CC0000" size="2"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=93296" target=Qualtar>60th Level Dwarven Knight</a></font></p><BR><img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/247/83/32478348.gif"><BR><SELECT>
